<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 23 at 8:54AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Patchy dense fog possible across portions of the western Rio
Grande Valley and Brush Country through 10 AM...
Visible satellite imagery and latest surface observations
continue to show patchy dense fog across portions of Starr County
as well as portions of the Brush Country this morning.
Visibilities will be reduced between 1 to 3 miles in general with
isolated areas falling to below 1 mile through 10 AM.
Motorists should be aware of locally dense fog with visibility
changing rapidly over short distances. Use low beam headlights and
leave extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.</description>
